text: Alfred Allen Davey (18 March 1856 – 27 June 1941) was member of the Queensland Legislative Council. ==Early life== Davey was born in Sussex, England to Allen Davey and his wife Ann (née Martin). ==Political career== Davey was called up to the Queensland Legislative Council in July 1906 and served till the Council was abolished in March 1922. ==Personal life== Davey married Matilda Margaret Lobb in London, and together had one child. He died in June 1941 and was cremated. ==References== Category:Members of the Queensland Legislative Council Category:1856 births Category:1941 deaths Category:People from Sussex Category:English emigrants to Australia
title: Alfred Davey
